snippet.title: sundial - scenic route (lyric video)
snippet.description:
thank you for listening :) stream "scenic route" here: https://fanlink.to/sundialscenicroute

stream "the roaring twenties" EP here: https://fanlink.to/roaringtwenties

written by dorothy, jisu, and chloe copoloff
mixed by evan sutton 

lyrics:
never was a straight A kid  
never called a genius 
stayed up every night 
bags under my eyes 
just to get an 86

tried out for the play that spring 
sang until my voice would sting
sure i nailed the notes
got into the show
but i still didn‚Äôt get the lead

nothing good comes easy, 
doesn‚Äôt mean that i won‚Äôt try
cuz nothing worth it happens overnight 

chorus
i don‚Äôt take the shortcut 
i‚Äôm here for the long run
i‚Äôd rather be the runner up, for the rest of my life, than cut to number one

i don‚Äôt need a free lunch
daddy and his trust fund
i‚Äôd rather be the underdog, for the rest of my life, than be the lucky one

cello lessons since first grade
practiced while my friends would play 
i wouldn‚Äôt leave the house
i hated missing out
but now i‚Äôm playing every state 

labels want a viral hit but i‚Äôll still take my time
cuz nothing worth it happens overnight 
    
chorus

outro
i will take the scenic route
driving through the ups and downs
cuz maybe that‚Äôs what life‚Äôs about
isn‚Äôt it? isn‚Äôt it?

silver line in every cloud
so rain or shine, i‚Äôm still around
cuz maybe that‚Äôs what life‚Äôs about
isn‚Äôt it? isn‚Äôt it?

growing pains Lyrics:

Sometimes, I wonder whether me when I was younger
Would like the person that I've become
'Cause first impressions tend to last through adolescence
And she still kinda hates everyone

[Pre-Chorus]
You and I aren't so different
Hindsight has perfect vision
You don't even know all the places that you'll go
But I'm sorry that you feel so alone

[Chorus]
Everything's gonna get better, everything's gonna get wors–µ
When it gets hard, rem–µmber that's the way it always works
Maybe we're just like flowers startin' down in the dirt
Everyone calls them growin' pains because we know the hurt
[Verse 2]
Sometimes, I question when I look at my reflection
If the person looking back is really me (Is really me)
A couple years spent learning how to disappear
A couple more spent learning what I could be

[Pre-Chorus]
You and I aren't so different
Hindsight has perfect vision
You don't even know all the places that you'll go
But I'm sorry that you feel so alone

[Chorus]
Everything's gonna get better, everything's gonna get worse
When it gets hard, remember that's the way it always works
Maybe we're just like flowers startin' down in the dirt
Everyone calls them growin' pains because we know the hurt

[Bridge]
I can't help myself from fakin' a smile
Hard to break an old habit you've had for a while
I don't wanna be any less than me
Sometimes, it's hard to believe

[Chorus]
Everything's gonna get better, everything's gonna get worse
When it gets hard, remember that's the way it always works
Maybe we're just like flowers startin' down in the dirt
Everyone calls them growin' pains because we know the hurt
